snippet.textDisplay: Honestly this design has a feel of fresh air. I think Motorola took a gamble, and they landed on the motherload. This is what a cellphone is supposed to be, small, portable, convenient. The only things that worry me are battery-life (for which i would tolerate a tad larger size), the life expectancy of the screen as well as fragility of both the screen and the wear of the mechanism since it is a new design.  But you cant have a new concept without risks and doubts. I am honestly interested to see where this takes the cellphone market. Competition breeds progress, i hope this gives us some great products.  A big bravo to Motorola.
